  <h>fèin</h>
  <p lang="en"><g>fèin</g>
    <en>self</en> has a number of uses.</p>


  <p>Older pedagogical examples – <xl id="obj-older-pedag">
      <li>
        <gd>Tha mo mhàthair a’ sgrìobhadh litreach gu m’athair a tha air falbh. Thubhairt mo
          mhàthair, “An téid thu do bhocsa nan litrichean leis an litir seo, Iain?” “Théid,” ars
          Iain, “falbhaidh mi an dràsda”. “Fuirich gus an dùin mi i is gus an cuir mi seòladh oirre.
            <m>Ceannaich fhéin stamp</m> agus cuir oirre i.” [...]</gd>
        <tr>My mother is writing a letter to my father who is away. My mother said, “Will you go to
          the postbox with this letter, John?” “Yes, I will,” said John, “I will leave now.” “Wait
          until I seal it and put an address on it. Buy a stamp [too?] and put it on it.” [...]</tr>
        <ref text="621">td. 5</ref>
      </li>
    </xl>
  </p>

